Exploration and development company Caledonia Mining has signed a memorandum of understanding with Fremiro Investments to buy Fremiroâ€™s 15% shareholding in the Blanket gold mine, in Zimbabwe, for $16.6-million. Caledonia already owns 49% of the Blanket mine and the transaction will increase its interest in the mine to 64%. Fremiro, meanwhile, will gain a 6.4% shareholding in Caledonia.